 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.1","title":"[audit][types] Strengthen cancelled reasons in Outcome::join and fix ok_or_else contract","description":"Audit follow-up from batch asupersync-1qfd0.332 for src/types/outcome.rs. Concrete defects: (1) Outcome::join/join_outcomes are left-biased even when both sides are Cancelled, so weaker reasons like user cancellation can beat stronger reasons like shutdown and lose cleanup-priority metadata; align with CancelReason::strengthen and combinator join semantics. (2) Outcome::ok_or_else docs currently claim preserved non-Ok distinctions, but the implementation erases Err/Cancelled/Panicked into a single fallback error; fix the contract in the same file while touching the surface. Scope: update implementation/docs/tests in src/types/outcome.rs only, with focused regression coverage and rch-backed validation.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:52:32.251304229Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:57:32.259514038Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:57:32.259490525Z","close_reason":"Patched src/types/outcome.rs so Cancelled+Cancelled joins strengthen to the worse CancelReason, corrected ok_or_else docs to reflect collapsing behavior, and validated with focused rch-backed tests plus cargo check; package clippy remains blocked only by unrelated existing issues in src/plan/fixtures.rs and src/transport/aggregator.rs, and cargo fmt --check is blocked by unrelated formatting drift in src/transport/aggregator.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:52:32.251304229Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
