+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.13","title":"[audit][kafka] Reject duplicate topic/partition entries in rebalance and commit batches","description":"Focused audit child under asupersync-1qfd0.332 for src/messaging/kafka_consumer.rs. rebalance() and commit_offsets() currently normalize batched TopicPartitionOffset inputs through map insertion, so duplicate topic/partition entries silently overwrite earlier values instead of being rejected. That can hide malformed rebalance batches and intra-call offset regressions. Scope: fail closed on duplicate topic/partition entries in rebalance and commit batches, add focused regressions, and validate with local hygiene plus rch-backed cargo gates.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldForge","created_at":"2026-03-14T04:20:49.573008109Z","created_by":"EmeraldForge","updated_at":"2026-03-14T04:20:49.573008109Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","kafka","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.13","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T04:20:49.573008109Z","created_by":"EmeraldForge","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
