 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","title":"[audit][http] Preserve identity default preference when Accept-Encoding only sets wildcard quality","description":"Audit follow-up in src/http/compress.rs. negotiate_encoding() currently applies wildcard quality to identity before the special-case default from RFC 9110 section 12.5.3. That makes headers like '*;q=0.5' incorrectly lower identity to q=0.5 and potentially prefer a compressed encoding, even though an unencoded representation is acceptable by default unless explicitly excluded by identity;q=0 or *;q=0 without a more specific identity entry. Scope: fix identity negotiation semantics and add focused regression tests in src/http/compress.rs only, validating with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:10:18.396700821Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:09:58.547118429Z","close_reason":"Patched src/http/compress.rs so Accept-Encoding wildcard quality no longer lowers implicit identity acceptability unless the wildcard explicitly rejects it at q=0, updated the stale wildcard-reject expectation, and validated with focused negotiate_ tests via rch. Package cargo check/clippy remain blocked by unrelated existing src/web/handler.rs unstable once_cell_try usage; cargo fmt --check remains blocked by unrelated formatting drift in src/cli/doctor/mod.rs, src/plan/fixtures.rs, and src/transport/aggregator.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
