 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.4","title":"[audit][obligation] Keep ObligationLedger reset from reusing live obligation IDs","description":"Audit follow-up in src/obligation/ledger.rs. ObligationLedger::reset() currently clears obligations and resets next_gen to zero. If any pre-reset ObligationToken survives, a post-reset acquire can reuse the same ObligationId and let the stale token commit/abort the new obligation record because commit()/abort() key only by token.id. Scope: preserve obligation ID uniqueness across reset, add a focused regression proving stale pre-reset tokens cannot alias post-reset acquisitions, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:12:40.723222557Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T15:34:35.344587646Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T15:34:35.344561207Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:12:40.723222557Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
