 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.359.1","title":"[audit][gen_server] Propagate full runtime capabilities into GenServer child Cx","description":"Scope::spawn_gen_server builds the child Cx with observability + blocking pool only, unlike normal scope::spawn task construction. GenServer lifecycle hooks can therefore lose timer-driver/logical-clock/registry/remote/evidence capabilities and observe weaker semantics than sibling tasks. Audit cx/scope parity and restore deterministic capability propagation.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"HazyRaven","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:20:19.110110830Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T03:47:19.246859671Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T03:47:19.246859671Z","close_reason":"Reused Scope::build_child_task_cx for GenServer spawns so child GenServer tasks now inherit the same timer driver, logical clock, registry handle, remote capability, blocking pool, trace buffer, and evidence sink as normal scoped children. Added a focused regression in src/gen_server.rs. Narrow rch lib/example checks passed; broader cargo test --lib and cargo check --all-targets are currently blocked by unrelated compile errors in src/combinator/bracket.rs:1198 and src/raptorq/decoder.rs:3964.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.359.2","title":"[audit][gen_server] Named stop/release must remove stale registry entries","description":"NamedGenServerHandle::stop_and_release() and abort_lease() resolved the lease obligation without cleaning the corresponding NameRegistry task mapping. That left stale whereis() results, blocked name reuse until manual unregister, and broke the invariant that releasing or aborting a name lease removes the registry entry for that task. Fix: clean the registry during stop/release and abort paths, add regressions, and update named-server call sites/tests to stop+drain before release.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"HazyRaven","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:46:50.613113494Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T03:47:19.246859671Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T03:47:19.246859671Z","close_reason":"Fixed NamedGenServerHandle stop_and_release()/abort_lease() to clean the registry, added regressions, and updated app/example shutdown call sites to stop and drain before releasing names.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.359.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.359","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:46:50.613113494Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
