 {"id":"asupersync-2c9j7.13","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][threshold] Do not double-count min_overhead on decode readiness","description":"Focused child slice under asupersync-2c9j7. In src/decoding.rs::required_symbols() and src/types/symbol_set.rs::calculate_threshold(), the current threshold formula computes ceil(K * overhead_factor) + min_overhead even though the config contract defines min_overhead as minimum extra symbols beyond K and the docs describe overhead_factor values like 1.05 as already meaning 5% extra symbols. That double-counts overhead whenever min_overhead > 0 and can delay decode readiness / overstate symbols_needed_estimate. Scope: align threshold calculation to max(ceil(K * factor), K + min_overhead) or equivalent fail-closed semantics, update focused docs/comments as needed, and add regressions in both surfaces.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FoggyTower","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:57:18.838689026Z","created_by":"FoggyTower","updated_at":"2026-03-14T03:57:18.838689026Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2c9j7.13","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2c9j7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:57:18.838689026Z","created_by":"FoggyTower","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
